Document: Leslie Pietrzyk
Leslie Pietrzyk is an American writer and editor. She is the author of the novels Pears on a Willow Tree, which was awarded the 2000 Minnesota Book Award for Fiction, and Silver Girl, which was published in 2008. She has also written a collection of short stories, This Angel on My Chest, which won the 2015 Drue Heinz Literature Prize and was published by the University of Pittsburgh Press in 2016. Pietrzyk's short fiction and essays have appeared in various literary journals and anthologies, including The Washington Post Magazine, where she is a regular contributor. She lives in Alexandria, Virginia, and is a member of the core faculty in the low-residency MFA program at the University of Tampa.

Document: Marianne Wiggins
Marianne Wiggins (born 1947) is an American author. According to The Cambridge Guide to Women's Writing in English, Wiggins writes with "a bold intelligence and an ear for hidden comedy." She has won a Whiting Award, an National Endowment for the Arts award and the Janet Heidinger Kafka Prize. She was a finalist for the Pulitzer Prize in fiction in 2004 for her novel Evidence of Things Unseen.
